

# <type>(<scope>): <subject>
#
# <body>
#
# ----------------------------------------
#
# <type>: specify one of the following -
#    feat     (new feature)
#    fix      (bug fix)
#    docs     (documentation only)
#    refactor (refactoring production code)
#    style    (formatting, missing semicolons, etc. no code change)
#    test     (adding or refactoring tests; no production code change)
#    chore    (updating npm scripts etc. no production code change)
#    revert   (revert a commit
#              <subject> must be the reverted commit's title
#              <description> must contain "This reverts commit <hash>.")
# <scope> (optional): module or otherwise related to subject.
#    if module, use the namespace of the module (e.g. P139, Lms)
# <subject>: brief summary of changes made
#    must be written in imperative mood (fix, add, remove, etc.)
#    first word must not be capitalize
#    must not exceed 70 characters
# <body> (optional): details of changes if necessary, or other changes to be mentioned
#    must not exceed 80 characters
